node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by richwebdeveloper on February 25, 2021 tagging @effectus_software. May be an image of text that says '000 </>음 Are you a new developer? You MUST know this! EFFECTUS®'.

Photo by richwebdeveloper on February 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says '1 coding is challenging. Don't worry if you struggle, Coding is not easy. If it were, everyone would be doing it. It does not matter how slowly you go so long as you do not stop. A senior developer is a junior developer who never gave up. EFFECTUS®'.

Photo by richwebdeveloper on February 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Perseverance is the key to success 2 This is VERY important! Our greatest weakness lies in giving up. The most certain way to succeed is always to try just one more time. Learning to code on a very basic level can take years, and it takes many more to become prolific. Keep learning, coding, and reading every day. Spend at least an hour a day learning to code. Make it a part of your life and habits EFFECTUS®'.

Photo by richwebdeveloper on February 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3 Make friends and find mentors mentors The coding road is hard, and it's almost impossible to do it alone. Find people you like and get together with them. The trick to this is going to gatherings aimed primarily at developers. Meeting new people might be out of your comfort zone, but you'd be surprised how friendly the developer community is. EFFECTUSO'.

Photo by richwebdeveloper on February 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4 Study Smarter, Not Harder Having hobbies outside of coding will help you a lot, not only in your career but in your personal life as well. Whenever you feel frustrated and tired of coding, go do another activity you enjoy, and afterwards you will feel super refreshed and ready to go back at it. EFFECTUS®'.

Photo by richwebdeveloper on February 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Master the Day 5 There's an ocean of information out there, and it's impossible to remember it all. Take it one day at a time. Slow down and concentrate. Think about the problem, think about the approaches to coding, and then start coding. The hardest part of coding is thinking deeply about the problem and planning how to solve it. Good planning and thinking will shave off years and save you quite a bit of time. "It's not that I'm so smart, it's just that I stay with problems longer" Albert Einstein EFFECTUS®'.

Photo by richwebdeveloper on February 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'ဝㅇဝ 6 Practice! </> Practice is what will help you grow your understanding of programming Knowing the rules and applying the rules is fundamentally different. You can read as much as you want, but you still need to put in the hours of exercises to fully understand how to code. The best programmers are not the ones with the most "talent" but the ones that solve most programming problems. "Practice isn't the thing you do once you're good. It's the thing you do that makes you good" Malcolm Gladwel EFFECTUS'.
Photo shared by richwebdeveloper on February 25, 2021 tagging @effectus_software. May be an image of text that says 'Follow @effectus_software for more! EFFECTUSO'.

node.text:
Umat yang Sakit

Oleh : @penapembaharu

Sakit. Kita sedang sakit. Kita merasakan sakitnya penjajahan, kemiskinan, kebodohan, kebutaan huruf, ketimpangan—segala ketidakmampuan. Semua hanya gejalanya. Namun, kita tidak menahu (bahkan tidak mau tahu) apa induk penyakit kita.

Para dokter-dokter kesohor hanya menyembuhkan gejala, bukan induk semang penyakit kita. Jamaluddin al Afghani hanya menyembuhkan batuk politik kita. Pun begitu Muhammad Abduh. Menurutnya pendidikan adalah demam kita.

Semua meredakan gejala-gejala saja, mereka tidak menyembuhkan inti penyakit kita. Padahal rasa sakit itu semakin perih dirasa. Perih sekali. Luar biasa. Bangkit dari kasur, kita berlari ke apotik pemikiran nan jauh di seberang sana.

Barat nama apoteknya. Sesampainya di sana dengan wajah pucat, banjir keringat, gagap— kita meracau. Apoteker bertanya: "mau obat apa?." Kita bingung. Akhirnya kita sebut semua gejala penyakit kita. Semua etalase dibuka. Semua obat diserahkannya pada kita.

Karena tak kuat menahan sakit, obat- obatan yang kita beli dari apotek Barat itu, segera kita telan setiap bijinya. Bukan malah sembuh, gejala- gejala baru penyakit kita malah bertambah banyak tumbuh. Sembuh satu, kambuh seribu.

Akhirnya penyakit kita tidak pernah sembuh. Apotek- apotek pemikiran Barat semakin untung, kita semakin buntung. Begitulah perumpamaan Malik bin Nabi di bukunya "Syurūt an- Nahdhah"— menggambarkan kondisi kita umat Islam yang tidak mampu menganalisis permasalahannya secara komprehensif.

و قد نتج عن هذا أنهم منذ خمسين عاما لا يعالجون المرض و إنما يعالجون الأعراض.

"Dan (kondisi) ini telah mengakibatkan mereka (umat Islam) semenjak 50 tahun tidak pernah menyembuhkan penyakit (nya), melainkan hanya menyembuhkan gejala- gejala (saja)"

Allahu A'lam

*Mālik bin Nabī: Syurūt an- Nahdhah, 45, 46.
.
